      • vMeas_DPS128_DcVI_Std

        public void vMeas_DPS128_DcVI_Std​(java.lang.String signal,
                                  java.lang.String iForce,
                                  java.lang.String vExpected,
                                  java.lang.String iRange,
                                  java.lang.String vRange,
                                  java.lang.String vClamp,
                                  java.lang.Boolean setDisconnect,
                                  java.lang.String iForceAction,
                                  java.lang.String vMeasAction)
        Measure voltage with DPS128 DcVI instrument connected in a standard mode

        For force actions on DPS128-HC and DPS128-HV variants, level.vrange and level.irange must be given. It is adequate that only these two properties are defined in the level group. Specifying level.vforce is not enforced. Note that it is not allowed to change voltage or current ranges in an action. The ranges are selected by the level group properties.

        Parameters:
        signal - Pin name
        iForce - The value to assign to the forceValue property like "-10 mA" or "10 mA"
        vExpected - The value to assign to the vexpected property like "1.3 V".
        iRange - The value to assign to the irange property.
        vRange - The value to assign to the vrange property.
        vClamp - The value to assign to the vclamp property.
        setDisconnect - The value to assign to the disconnect property after measurement execution
        iForceAction - Identifier of the iforce action
        vMeasAction - Identifier of the vmeas action
